-----
MONDAY OF HOLY WEEK

LAUDS
READING:    Jer 11:19-20    

BENEDICTUS:	Father, righteous One, the world does not know you, but I know you, because you are the One who sent me.

PRAYER:	Grant, we pray, almighty God, that, though in our weakness we fail, we may be revived through the Passion of your Only Begotten Son. Who lives and reigns with you in the unity of the Holy Spirit, one God, for ever and ever.

SEXT
READING:    Jer 18:20b

Response same as Palm Sunday

VESPERS
HYMN p. ?
READING:    Rom 5:8-9    

MAGNIFICAT:	As Moses lifted up the serpent in the desert, so must the Son of Man be raised up, so that all who believe in him may have eternal life.

TUESDAY OF HOLY WEEK

LAUDS
READING:    Zech 10:10-11a    

BENEDICTUS:	Father, give me the glory that I had with you before the world was made.

PRAYER:	Almighty ever-living God, grant us so to celebrate the mysteries of the Lord's Passion that we may merit to receive your pardon. Through our Lord Jesus Christ, your Son, who lives and reigns with you in the unity of the Holy Spirit, one God, for ever and ever.

SEXT
READING:    1 Cor 1:22-24    

Response same as Palm Sunday

VESPERS
HYMN p. ?
READING:    1 Cor 1:27b-30    

MAGNIFICAT:	I have power to lay down my life, and I have power to take it up again.

WEDNESDAY OF HOLY WEEK

LAUDS
READING:    Is 50:4b-7    

BENEDICTUS:	Through the eternal Spirit, Christ offered himself to God as the perfect sacrifice. His blood purifies us form sin and makes us fit servants of the living God.

PRAYER:	O God, who willed your Son to submit for our sake to the yoke of the Cross, so that you might drive from us the power of the enemy, grant us, your servants, to attain the grace of the resurrection. Through our Lord Jesus Christ, your Son, who lives and reigns with you in the unity of the Holy Spirit, one God, for ever and ever.

SEXT
READING:    Rom 15:3    

Response same as Palm Sunday

VESPERS
HYMN p. ?
READING:    Eph 4:32-5:2    

MAGNIFICAT:	The Master says: My hour is close at hand; I and my disciples shall celebrate the Passover in your house.

HOLY THURSDAY
PSALMODY WEEK III

LAUDS
READING:    Heb 2:9-10    

BENEDICTUS:	I have longed to eat this meal with you before I suffer.

PRAYER:	O God, who anointed your Only Begotten Son with the Holy Spirit and made him Christ and Lord, graciously grant that, being made sharers in his consecration, we may bear witness to your Redemption in the world. Through our Lord Jesus Christ, your Son, who lives and reigns with you in the unity of the Holy Spirit, one God, for ever and ever.

SEXT
READING:    Heb 7:26-27    
